## Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/carousel-search-bar-ios-app.git
   cd carousel-search-bar-ios-app
Open the project in Xcode:

Double-click the YourApp.xcodeproj file to open the project in Xcode.

Run the app:

Select your target device or simulator, and click the "Run" button in Xcode to build and run the app.

Usage
Carousel View: Swipe left or right on the carousel to browse through images.
Search Bar: Type in the search bar to filter the list of items. The search bar will pin to the top as you scroll down the list.
Code Structure
ContentView.swift: The main view containing the carousel, search bar, and list.
PinnedSearchBarView.swift: A reusable view component for the sticky search bar.
ContentViewModel.swift: The view model managing the app's state, including the list of items and search query.
Item.swift: The model representing each list item.
CarouselView.swift: A reusable view component for the image carousel.


Styling the App
You can customize the appearance of the carousel, search bar, and list by modifying the SwiftUI views directly in the relevant files. Experiment with different modifiers to change the styling as needed.

